    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="533"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Moscow Embassy Files—879.6 Berlin Route</note>
                <head>No. 533<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HK1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Soviet Assistant Foreign Commissar</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_VAY1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vyshinsky</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 383</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-07">July 7,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_V2">Vyshinski</persName>
                    </hi>: I have informed <persName corresp="#p_EGADD1">General
                        Eisenhower</persName> of our last conversation with regard to the opening up
                    of a civil air lines connection at Berlin between Soviet and American planes. I
                    have suggested that <persName corresp="#p_EGADD1">General Eisenhower</persName>
                    or his representative discuss this matter with <persName corresp="#p_ZMGK1"
                        >Marshal Zhukov</persName> or his representative. I hope that <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZMGK1">Marshal Zhukov</persName> will be informed of the
                    desirability of this connection and authorized to work out the technical
                    details.</p>
                <p>I trust that this connection can be established promptly as every day adds to the
                    inconvenience and difficulties of our communications with the United States and
                    other United States Missions in Western <pb facs="0938" n="804" xml:id="pg_804"
                    /> Europe. I therefore request your cooperation in the speedy conclusion of
                    arrangements for this service.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName xml:id="HWA2">W. A. <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
